{"updated_at": "2012-02-09T22:20:22Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-02-09T22:17:56Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3896932", "id": 3896932, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3524", "issue_id": 3524, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/blakeeb", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "42a8f84860cde30515a5d26519f1c207", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/42a8f84860cde30515a5d26519f1c207?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Febb8281247a7fe2824525f8836db4290.png", "id": 105412, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/events{/privacy}", "login": "blakeeb", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/blakeeb/followers"}, "body": "Some databases do not have a \"public\" schema. While it is the default in postgres, it's not required, and in several enterprise environments I've encountered, \"public\" is deleted for security and data cleanliness reasons (which I don't really agree with doing... but data teams can be quite opinionated), and tables are stored in more specifically-named schemas.\r\n\r\nWith this patch applied, ActiveRecord has been working fine without a \"public\" schema existing.", "_id": {"$oid": "5238356fbd3543c15100fc45"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3524#issuecomment-3896932"}
